Class SortedMessageQueue

  • java.lang.Object

            • com.camerontec.catalys.core.message.SortedMessageQueue
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable, Cloneable, Iterable<IFIXMessage>, Collection<IFIXMessage>, Deque<IFIXMessage>, List<IFIXMessage>, Queue<IFIXMessage>

    public class SortedMessageQueue
extends LinkedList<IFIXMessage>
    Sorted queue of IFIXMessages.

    Messages are sorted by sequence number. Duplicates are discarded.

    This class is thread-safe.

      • SortedMessageQueue

        public SortedMessageQueue()
        Creates a queue without a size limit. Same as calling new SortedMessageQueue(0)

      • SortedMessageQueue

        public SortedMessageQueue(int maxSize)
        Creates a queue limited to the given maximum size.

        When the queue is full and a new entry is added (with put(com.camerontec.catalys.core.message.IFIXMessage)), the first element of the queue is automatically removed.

        Parameters:
        maxSize - Maximum size of queue if > 0, otherwise the queue has no limit.

      • get

        public IFIXMessage get(long timeout)
                throws InterruptedException
        Gets first message from the queue.

        If nothing there waits for up to timeout milliseconds.
        If timeout < 0, never timeout. In case that timeout is > 0 the get method can return before the timeout expires. This happens in case of spurious wakeups. This will rarely occur in practice, and applications must guard against it if needed. Spurious wakeups are handled by this class when timeout < 0.

        Parameters:
        timeout - timeout
        Returns:
        element or null if nothing in the queue after timeout
        Throws:
        InterruptedException - if thread is interrupted

      • put

        public void put(IFIXMessage message)
        Add message to queue if does not contain a message with the same seqNumber.

        All duplicates will be dropped and information about dropped message will be logged at DEBUG level.

        If there is a thread waiting on a get, this will wake it up.

        Parameters:
        message - the message to add
